Now, when they find themselves stripped of the word of God, and of every probable argument, they resort to their usual pretext, that it is every ancient usage, and confirmed by the consent of many ages. Though this allegation were true, it would not at all serve their cause. A sacrament is not from earth, but from heaveu; not of men, but of God alone. If they wish their confirmation to be regarded as a sacrament, they must prove God to be the Author of it.
